-- Slovakia to Reduce Flows to Private Pension Funds, Sme Reports
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-05-28T06:37:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/slovakia-to-reduce-flows-to-private-pension-funds-sme-reports.html
The Slovak government will
temporarily cut contributions to private pension funds to a
maximum 5 percent of wages from 9 percent now,  Sme  reported,
citing Labor Minister Jan Richter.  The cut, aimed at reducing the deficit of the public
welfare system, will be effective by at least 2016, the
newspaper cited Richter as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
